column2: allocatedSwap        The number of megabytes of swap space have actually been written to. Swap space must be reserved before it can be allocated.
column3: bufferMemory        The number of megabytes of memory allocated to buffers.
column4: sharedMemory        The number of megabytes of shared memory on the machine.
column5: cpuActive        The percentage of the total available time that has been used in a non-idle state.
column6: cpuIdle        The percentage of the total available time that has been spent sleeping.
column7: cpuNice        The percentage of the total available time that has been used to execute user code in processes with low priority.
column8: cpuSystem        The percentage of the total available time that has been used to execute system (i.e. kernel) code.
column9: cpuUser        The percentage of the total available time that has been used to execute user code.
column10: iowait        The percentage of the total available time that has been used to wait for I/O to complete.
column11: irq        The percentage of the total available time that has been used servicing  interrupts.
column12: softirq        The percentage of the total available time that has been used servicing softirqs.
column13: cpus        The number of online cpus on the local machine.
column14: freeMemory        The number of megabytes of unused memory on the machine.
column15: physicalMemory        The actual amount of total physical memory on the machine.
column16: processes        The number of processes in the computer at the time of data collection.  Notice that this is an instantaneous count, not an average over the time interval.  Each process represents the running of a program.
column17: unallocatedSwap        The number of megabytes of swap space that have not been allocated.
column18: cachedMemory        The number of megabytes of memory used for the file system cache.
column19: dirtyMemory        The number of megabytes of memory in the file system cache that need to be written.
column20: cpuNonUser        The percentage of total available time that has been used to execute non-user code.(includes system, iowait, irq, softirq etc.)
column21: loopbackPackets        The number of network packets sent (or received) on the loopback interface
column22: loopbackBytes        The number of network bytes sent (or received) on the loopback interface
column23: recvPackets        The total number of network packets received (excluding loopback)
column24: recvBytes        The total number of network bytes received (excluding loopback)
column25: recvErrors        The total number of network receive errors
column26: recvDrops        The total number network receives dropped
column27: xmitPackets        The total number of network packets transmitted (excluding loopback)
column28: xmitBytes        The total number of network bytes transmitted (excluding loopback)
column29: xmitErrors        The total number of network transmit errors
column30: xmitDrops        The total number of network transmits dropped
column31: xmitCollisions        The total number of network transmit collisions
column32: contextSwitches        The total number of context switches from one thread to another on the computer.  Thread switches can occur either inside of a single process or across processes.  A thread switch may be caused either by one thread asking another for information, or by a thread being preempted by another, higher priority thread becoming ready to run.
column33: processCreates        The total number of times a process has been created.
column34: pagesPagedIn        The total number of pages that have been brought into memory from disk by the operating system's memory manager.
column35: pagesPagedOut        The total number of pages that have been flushed from memory to disk by the operating system's memory manager.
column36: pagesSwappedIn        The total number of swap pages that have been read in from disk by the operating system's memory manager.
column37: pagesSwappedOut        The total number of swap pages that have been written out to disk by the operating system's memory manager.
column38: diskReadsCompleted        The total number disk read operations completed successfully
column39: diskReadsMerged        The total number disk read operations that were able to be merge with adjacent reads for efficiency
column40: diskBytesRead        The total number bytes read from disk successfully
column41: diskTimeReading        The total number of milliseconds spent reading from disk
column42: diskWritesCompleted        The total number disk write operations completed successfully
column43: diskWritesMerged        The total number disk write operations that were able to be merge with adjacent reads for efficiency
column44: diskBytesWritten        The total number bytes written to disk successfully
column45: diskTimeWriting        The total number of milliseconds spent writing to disk
column46: diskOpsInProgress        The current number of disk operations in progress
column47: diskTimeInProgress        The total number of milliseconds spent with disk ops in progress
column48: diskTime        The total number of milliseconds that measures both completed disk operations and any accumulating backlog of in progress ops.
column49: loadAverage1        The average number of threads in the run queue or waiting for disk I/O over the last minute.
column50: loadAverage15        The average number of threads in the run queue or waiting for disk I/O over the last fifteen minutes.
column51: loadAverage5        The average number of threads in the run queue or waiting for disk I/O over the last five minutes.
